01:13.545 --> 01:17.380
"But I heard him exclaim
'ere he drove out of sight,

01:17.482 --> 01:21.817
'Happy Christmas to all,
and to all a good night.'"

01:24.389 --> 01:25.888
Thank you again, Mayor Rose.

01:25.990 --> 01:27.557
Would you care to stay for some dinner?

01:27.659 --> 01:28.591
We're having pizza.

01:28.693 --> 01:30.225
I'm sorry. Pizza... that... that's all?

01:30.327 --> 01:32.060
When my mom used to bring me here,

01:32.162 --> 01:33.762
I would help serve turkey,
green beans...

01:33.864 --> 01:34.929
you know, the works.

01:35.031 --> 01:36.265
There was even a tree... a <i> real</i> tree...

01:36.367 --> 01:37.266
and kids got presents.

01:37.368 --> 01:38.900
Oh, we got presents.

01:39.002 --> 01:42.904
Some local dentists donated
over 200 toothbrushes.

01:43.006 --> 01:45.940
- Useful gifts are so underrated.
- I'm sorry.

01:46.042 --> 01:47.308
Are you telling me that these families

01:47.410 --> 01:48.876
are celebrating Christmas
under a plastic tree

01:48.978 --> 01:49.943
with pizza and toothbrushes?

01:50.045 --> 01:51.312
It's been a very hard year.

01:51.414 --> 01:52.680
We lost our federal funding,

01:52.782 --> 01:54.782
and we have more families
to support than ever.

01:54.884 --> 01:56.116
You see them? The Baxters.

01:56.218 --> 01:58.252
Husband got laid off,
fell behind on their rent,

01:58.354 --> 01:59.587
and got evicted.

01:59.689 --> 02:01.289
That's the type of family
we didn't have last year.

02:01.442 --> 02:02.321
Wow.

02:02.423 --> 02:04.021
I didn't realize

02:04.123 --> 02:06.324
things had gotten
that much worse in a year.

02:06.426 --> 02:09.158
Mm-hmm.

02:09.261 --> 02:11.128
Hey! Everybody!

02:11.230 --> 02:12.129
- Courtney.
- Hey!

02:12.231 --> 02:13.397
Mayor Rose...

02:13.499 --> 02:14.665
you are not about to overpromise
right now, are you?

02:14.767 --> 02:15.733
Oh, you don't even know.

02:15.835 --> 02:19.403
Ah, people, I was raised to believe

02:19.505 --> 02:22.339
that every family deserves
to have a great Christmas.

02:22.441 --> 02:25.241
A dinner, presents, a real tree.

02:25.344 --> 02:26.976
- That tree sucks!
- Yes, it does!

02:27.078 --> 02:28.911
So, friends, as Mayor of Fort Grey,

02:29.013 --> 02:32.248
I hereby pledge
to give every family in here

02:32.351 --> 02:34.551
a Christmas you'll never forget.

02:35.920 --> 02:37.086
No time for questions.

02:37.188 --> 02:38.520
I'm here all day!

02:38.622 --> 02:40.956
Big news...
I promised the shelter residents

02:41.058 --> 02:41.990
a real Christmas.

02:42.092 --> 02:43.425
Also, Val's mad at me.

02:43.527 --> 02:45.761
Classic Courtney overpromise. I love it!

02:45.863 --> 02:46.795
I'm not mad, Courtney.

02:46.897 --> 02:48.163
I-I think it was a great thing to say.

02:48.265 --> 02:50.999
Wait. F-For real?

02:51.101 --> 02:52.568
Be careful. This could be
one of her word traps.

02:52.670 --> 02:53.935
For real.

02:54.037 --> 02:56.671
I... Wasn't it Gandhi who said
a society can be judged

02:56.773 --> 02:59.073
on how it treats
its most vulnerable citizens?

02:59.175 --> 03:01.141
Ah, yes, yes,
and somebody else said that...

03:01.244 --> 03:02.610
that's basically what I said.

03:02.712 --> 03:03.878
I love what you're trying to do,

03:03.980 --> 03:05.346
but the shelter feeds over 300 families

03:05.448 --> 03:06.581
and the city can't afford that.

03:06.683 --> 03:07.882
Hey, look, Val.

03:07.984 --> 03:09.216
I know it seems impossible,

03:09.318 --> 03:11.729
but isn't it my job as mayor
to at least try?

03:11.784 --> 03:12.853
Hey!

03:12.954 --> 03:14.888
Also, I'm gonna need your ideas
to help do that.

03:14.990 --> 03:16.018
Yep. Chop-chop.

03:16.058 --> 03:17.681
It's 4:00 p.m. on Christmas
Eve, so good luck.

03:17.706 --> 03:18.706
- Yeah.
- Well,

03:18.753 --> 03:22.028
w-we've already drained
the entire 2017 budget.

03:23.532 --> 03:26.433
This idea is a little naughty.

03:26.535 --> 03:28.734
- I doubt that.
- You think it's naughty?

03:28.836 --> 03:31.604
We could get an advance
on the 2018 budget,

03:31.706 --> 03:33.773
just to get Christmas going.

03:34.542 --> 03:36.542
Sounded a little naughtier in my head.

03:36.644 --> 03:37.743
- Yeah.
- But we would need

03:37.845 --> 03:39.578
official sign-off
from two people. First, you.

03:39.680 --> 03:41.146
Oh, you already know
I am easily persuaded.

03:41.171 --> 03:42.147
Who else?

03:43.418 --> 03:45.583
Who is it?

03:45.685 --> 03:48.887
Oh, it's you guys. Go away.

03:48.988 --> 03:51.155
Wow. Drinking in your office
on Christmas Eve?

03:51.257 --> 03:52.657
That's lonely, even for you.

03:52.759 --> 03:54.258
Well, if you must know,
I promised my family

03:54.360 --> 03:56.761
a ski trip to Mammoth,
but I can't afford it.

03:56.863 --> 03:58.430
So they're home all packed, and...

03:58.532 --> 03:59.764
I haven't told 'em yet.

03:59.866 --> 04:01.900
So, is your plan just
to hide out in here forever?

04:02.001 --> 04:03.199
No, I need an excuse,

04:03.302 --> 04:04.902
so I'm gonna drink until I think of one.

04:04.970 --> 04:06.970
Well, you know, we would love
to stick around and brainstorm,

04:07.039 --> 04:09.907
but we need your signature
to release the 2018 budget

04:09.975 --> 04:11.608
to help the homeless.

04:11.710 --> 04:13.444
You know what? That's a great idea.

04:13.512 --> 04:15.579
I can say I got stabbed
by a homeless person,

04:15.648 --> 04:17.012
and now I can't go skiing.

04:17.115 --> 04:18.214
Thank you.

04:18.283 --> 04:19.916
Get a hold of yourself, man.

04:19.983 --> 04:22.318
Ed, just sign the paper,
and we'll leave you alone.

04:22.386 --> 04:25.287
Oh, if I could just get my wife to
say those words.

04:25.356 --> 04:27.289
Look, the city's already
borrowed against the budget.

04:27.358 --> 04:28.357
You know this.

04:28.426 --> 04:29.725
Fort Grey does not have a slush fund.

04:29.794 --> 04:31.226
If they did, I'd be skiing right now.

04:31.295 --> 04:33.359
Come on, man. It is the holidays, okay?

04:33.417 --> 04:34.616
There must be something we can do.

04:34.702 --> 04:36.798
I just gave a huge speech.
It was real charismatic.

04:36.900 --> 04:38.032
Here's an idea...

04:38.134 --> 04:39.768
maybe you should have thought
of this three months ago.

04:39.837 --> 04:40.969
But you didn't.

04:41.071 --> 04:42.270
And that's not surprising,

04:42.372 --> 04:44.573
because you really haven't
done much as the mayor.

04:44.675 --> 04:46.007
No, no, no, no. That's not true.

04:46.076 --> 04:47.676
We, uh... We... We solved a bus strike.

04:47.744 --> 04:49.845
- We got music in schools.
- Met a lady.

04:49.947 --> 04:52.113
That's all very cute,
but what about jobs?

04:52.182 --> 04:53.881
What about housing?
What about all those potholes?

04:53.950 --> 04:55.716
Something that makes
an actual difference.

04:55.818 --> 04:57.985
Gunt, c'mon, man. This is for families.

04:58.087 --> 04:59.052
It's Christmas.

04:59.121 --> 05:00.020
"It's Christmas."

05:00.089 --> 05:01.054
I know.

05:01.156 --> 05:02.623
Where did I put all my fuzzy feelings?

05:02.725 --> 05:04.859
Forget it, man.

05:04.961 --> 05:06.226
You're not leaving, are you?

05:06.328 --> 05:08.195
Door's always closed, guys.

05:08.297 --> 05:10.330
Gunt. Gunt.

05:10.432 --> 05:13.065
- He's a jerk... I know.
- No! He's right!

05:13.167 --> 05:14.868
Did you hear what that volunteer said?

05:14.936 --> 05:16.335
This year was worse than ever.

05:16.404 --> 05:18.137
The people of Fort Grey need jobs,

05:18.206 --> 05:20.940
and I'm the mayor who put
plastic covers over benches.

05:21.042 --> 05:23.075
I shoulda just stayed in my lane
and been a famous rapper,

05:23.144 --> 05:24.644
then Fort Grey would've been better off.

05:24.713 --> 05:26.813
Is anyone gonna touch that?

05:26.915 --> 05:28.413
Courtney, change is slow.

05:28.516 --> 05:30.248
Fort Grey has no money,
just a lot of red tape

05:30.350 --> 05:31.717
and a bitter City Council President.

05:31.819 --> 05:33.151
You're being too hard on yourself.

05:33.253 --> 05:36.488
Or am I finally being hard enough?

05:38.025 --> 05:39.791
- What?
- I'll see you guys later.

05:39.894 --> 05:41.359
Why does he ask a question

05:41.461 --> 05:42.995
if he's not gonna stay around
for the answer?

05:43.063 --> 05:45.295
I mean, I don't always have one,
but I like to hear myself talk...

05:45.364 --> 05:47.732
you know, find it, go on
that journey to discovery.

05:47.834 --> 05:50.019
Let's see what's
on the World Wide Webby,

05:50.120 --> 05:52.236
the old Dub-dub-dub.

05:52.338 --> 05:54.405
This is a garbage planet.

